{
  "_note": [
    "Band specification data for seed_band_registry.py (ADR-017, amended 2026-03-25).",
    "",
    "This file is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for band definitions fed to the seed",
    "script. It was extracted from the embedded BAND_SPECS list in seed_band_registry.py",
    "to separate data from code.",
    "",
    "██████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████",
    "██  ALIAS OWNERSHIP RULE (ADR-017 amendment, corrected 2026-04-01)         ██",
    "██                                                                         ██",
    "██  Bare single-letter aliases (U, B, V, R, I, J, H) MUST live on the     ██",
    "██  Generic_* entries, NEVER on instrument-specific entries.               ██",
    "██                                                                         ██",
    "██  Rationale: bare aliases carry no instrument provenance. Routing them   ██",
    "██  to instrument-specific entries (e.g. HCT_HFOSC_Bessell_V) produces    ██",
    "██  misleading band_id values on ingested data and inflates resolution     ██",
    "██  confidence to 'high' when 'low' (generic_fallback) is correct.        ██",
    "██                                                                         ██",
    "██  See: ADR-017 amendment § Alias Ownership Invariant                    ██",
    "██       ADR-018 Decision 5 (Generic fallback)                            ██",
    "██       DESIGN-004 §6.5 (ticket-driven resolution)                       ██",
    "██████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████",
    "",
    "GENERIC ENTRIES AS BESSELL/2MASS REFERENCE PROFILES",
    "Generic entries are NOT sparse. They carry SVO-sourced spectral data from the",
    "canonical reference profiles for their photometric system:",
    "  - Optical (UBVRI): HCT/HFOSC Bessell profiles (Bessell 1990 transmission",
    "    curves — the de facto standard for Johnson-Cousins CCD photometry).",
    "  - NIR (J, H): 2MASS profiles (the de facto standard NIR photometric system).",
    "  - NIR (K): Sparse with lambda_eff hint only (Johnson K vs 2MASS Ks are",
    "    distinct bands per band_grouping_rules.md Rule S3).",
    "",
    "The svo_filter_id on Generic entries documents the reference profile source;",
    "observatory_facility and instrument remain null because Generic entries make",
    "no claim about the observing instrument."
  ],
